article.headline: MARQUETTE 78, (25) WASHINGTON 61
article.story:
MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Krystal Ellis scored 24 points to lead
Marquette to a 78-61 victory over Washington in the season opener
for both teams Tuesday night.

Danielle Kamm had 15 points and 10 rebounds for the Golden
Eagles, and Svetlana Kovalenko added 13 points.

Cameo Hicks had 12 points and Jill Bell 10 to lead Washington,
which was whistled for 32 fouls to only 19 for Marquette.
